# Aprimo DAM API Reference

This MCP server integrates with **Aprimo DAM (Digital Asset Management) only** — `{tenant}.dam.aprimo.com/api/core`. It does not cover Marketing Operations, Analytics, or other Aprimo products.

Use the official Aprimo DAM API documentation as the primary reference when implementing or changing integrations in this MCP server:

- Search records (POST `/search/records`): https://developers-api.aprimo.com/#33d066f8-3670-45a3-8df6-69739fef7446
- Get record by ID (GET `/record/{id}`): https://developers-api.aprimo.com/#707b19c8-11c7-4e23-a1bd-22e0c944f2cb
- General reference: https://developers-api.aprimo.com/#0b64aa4b-2033-43c2-913d-338eb75676de

## When to consult it

- Adding or modifying MCP tools that call Aprimo
- Choosing endpoints, request headers, and response shapes
- Search expressions, select headers (`select-record`, `select-classification`, etc.)
- Record, field, and classification API behavior

## Project conventions

- Base URL: `https://{tenant}.dam.aprimo.com/api/core/...`
- Auth: OAuth client credentials; credentials may arrive via request headers or env vars
- Prefer existing patterns in `src/aprimo/` and `src/aprimo/headers.ts`
- Do not guess API shapes when the reference or existing code can confirm them
